We hypothesize that one mechanism supporting the binding of distributed representations is dendritic plateau potentials, a NMDA‐dependent regenerative event initially identified in CA1 cells which detects distinct separate inputs from CA3 and the EC and combines them as a coincidence detector while mice are running on a treadmill and coding space via CA1 place cells (Bittner et al., 2015; Sheffield & Dombeck, 2015). We propose these dendritic events as a general mechanism by which binding of information occurs (Figure 9). This rather long‐lasting (few hundred milliseconds) dendritic

