Cognitive deficits are frequent in TLE patients (Helmstaedter & Kockelmann, 2006). Related to extensive structural abnormalities beyond the HPC connectome, TLE patients present a panel of various cognitive alterations, from memory impairments to executive functions, language, intellectual quotient, object verbal naming and sensorimotor skills (Hermann, Seidenberg, Schoenfeld, & Davies, 1997; Oyegbile et al., 2004; Riley et al., 2010; Robertson, Evans, Walterfang, Ng, & Velakoulis, 2008); for review see (Bell, Lin, Seidenberg, & Hermann, 2011) and (Allone et al., 2017). Those cognitive

